zines.description:
Civil Disobedience is a Toronto punk fanzine. This might be an earlier issue, but it came out after August 6th, 1981 because there is a reference to a Globe and Mail article, which was the inspiration behind a piece on nuclear war. 
- This issue starts out with a collage on a Poison Girls song;
- There is another collage piece critiquing gender roles as related to masculinity;
- There is a review critiquing the film "D.O.A.";
- There is a collage on TVs;
- There is a collage for the Dead Kennedy

///ENG
First edition of Sound In Persistence. Reflections on contemporary sound production in convergence with graphic experimentation and intermedial esotericism.

///ESPPrimera edición de Sound In Persistence. Reflexiones en torno a la producción sonora contemporánea en convergencia con la experimentación gráfica y el esoterismo intermedial.

Thanks to all the scanners involved in getting this series fully scanned. Includes also Deadline USA published by Dark Horse. Volume 1 issue 3 is the only issue unscanned.

